cards.back:
Swap 'Lead' for any other Standard Event name:

fbq('track', 'Lead');

The event code does NOT need to live inside the Base Pixel block — it can fire almost anywhere on the page, as long as it's after the base code. Events can also fire on a button click or form submission.

value and currency are mandatory on Purchase:

fbq('track', 'Purchase', {
  value: 54.00,
  currency: 'USD'
});

Parameter payload syntax pattern:
- Open bracket {
- Parameter name + colon (e.g. value:)
- Parameter value + comma (e.g. 54.00,)
- Repeat for all parameters
- Closed bracket }, then close the call with );
